Region: us-east-1 (VERIFY THIS!)
Navigate to EC2 Service

Go to Services â†’ EC2

In left sidebar, find "Elastic Block Store" â†’ "Volumes"

Create Volume

Click "Create volume"

Volume settings:

Volume type: General Purpose SSD (gp3)

Size: 2 GiB

IOPS: Leave default (3000) or set minimum 3000

Throughput: Leave default (125) or set minimum 125 MB/s

Availability Zone: Choose any AZ in us-east-1 (e.g., us-east-1a)

Snapshot ID: Leave blank (creating new empty volume)

Volume encryption: Optional (disabled by default)

Add Tags

Click "Add tag"

Key: Name

Value: xfusion-volume

(Optional: Add more tags like Environment, Project, etc.)

Create and Verify

Click "Create volume"

You'll see "Successfully created volume"

Click "View volumes" to see it in list

Status should show as "available"

ğŸ“‹ What We Created
Name: xfusion-volume

Type: gp3 (General Purpose SSD)

Size: 2 GiB

Status: Available (not attached to any instance)

Location: us-east-1 availability zone

ğŸ”§ Next Steps
This volume can now be:

Attached to an EC2 instance in the same AZ

Used as a data disk (not boot volume in this case)

Encrypted later if needed (cannot encrypt after creation)

âš ï¸ Important Notes
AZ Locked: Can only attach to instances in same Availability Zone

Attachment: Must be attached to an instance to be used

File System: Need to create file system after attachment (mkfs)

Mounting: Need to mount to a directory after file system creation

